CHAT.comment: Chi and Mot are the only participants , and the meal lasts about 9 minutes. Mot keeps asking what do in school , and Chi initially says she can't talk while she's eating! So the situation seems a little forced. Nevertheless , Chi is very verbal , and conversation flows along pretty well. Well , MOT has a little trouble keeping Chi at the table. A few times Chi said that Mot said she could do or have something , but that's not exactly what Mot had said.... Tape may have been on voice activation , since there are several cuts.

u.a: calling out over water running in background
Chi was kicking at chair or something (hard enough to hear on tape)
aft sounds of eating and utensils clanging against plates
exasperated , but not out of control
away from tape , looking out window or door
tape recorder turned off . It's turned on again , but the only voices are away from the table , until Mot announces <Chi's done eating> and the tape is turned off again at 10:34
